<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="able-adj">able <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'eɪbl/    美 /'eɪbl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>能：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unable </p>
<ul>
<li>(be) able to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Looking back, I feel I wouldn’t be able to ride a bike had I lost heart.
回想起来，我觉得如果当初自己失去信心，就不能学会骑自行车了。</p><footer>2014 福建</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Being able to make small talk is a very useful skill in relating with other people. 
能与人闲谈是和他人打交道的非常实用的技能。</p><footer>2012 辽宁</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>能干的；有能力的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Even the most able students found the test difficult.
连能力最强的学生都觉得这次测验很难。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>ably / 'eɪbli/ adv   </p></div>